# Place Value Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p3p4qe"
more digits
=
larger value
```

or:

```text id="u7p1qe"
decimal places
work like
whole numbers
```

Some may think:

```text id="c9p5qe"
0.45
>
0.5
```

because:

```text id="k4p8qe"
45
>
5
```

without understanding:

```text id="n6p3qe"
decimal value
depends on
place position
```

Example:

students may compare:

```text id="t1p7qe"
0.8
and
0.75
```

and incorrectly choose:

```text id="q5p2qe"
0.75
```

instead of recognizing:

```text id="v8p4qe"
0.8
=
0.80
>
0.75
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="w3p7qe"
magnitude reasoning
```

For Grade 5:

focus includes:

Whole Number Place Value:

* millions
* expanded form
* standard form
* word form
* comparing numbers

Decimal Understanding:

* tenths
* hundredths
* thousandths
* place relationships
* comparing decimals

Important idea:

```text id="a9p1qe"
digit value
depends on
position
```

